or judgment had largely contributed to her daughter’s mistakes. She insisted that if she had succeeded in taking her whole family to Brighton, this disaster would have been avoided, claiming Lydia had been left without proper supervision. She accused the Forsters of gross negligence, asserting that Lydia would never have acted this way if she had been watched more closely. She complained that she was always overruled, then fretted that Mr. Bennet would surely seek out Wickham, be killed in a duel, and leave them to be evicted by the Collinses, ultimately begging her brother for his continued support."
